{"insight":"A teaching lives by correcting itself","plainSummary":"The deepest teachings stay alive by holding two truths together, so neither hardens into the mistake it was meant to heal.","atAGlance":"Some teachings protect themselves by refusing to become simple. One side gives the mind a clear path to walk. The other side keeps that path from becoming an idol. Wisdom may live in the faithful movement between them.","match":["contradiction keeps"],"tags":["wisdom","practice","tradition","balance"]}
